WLC_POINTER_SET_POSITION(3)                                   WLC API FUNCITONS

NAME

    wlc_pointer_set_position - sets the mouse pointer position

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_pointer_set_position(const struct wlc_point *position);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_pointer_set_position() is used to set the mouse pointer to a new
    position relative to the top left corner of the currently focused output.

RETURN VALUE

    None.

NOTES

    The mouse pointer position will be clamped to the focused output if the
    requested position is out of bounds.
